    "slideDesc1": "Learn Korean consonants and vowels by writing and speaking them.\nSystematically study the combination principles of 14 consonants and 21 vowels.\nPractice writing with stroke order guides while mastering accurate pronunciation.\nLearn complex characters like double consonants and compound vowels step by step.",
    "slideTitle2": "Pronunciation",
    "slideDesc2": "Korean pronunciation is organized by characteristics with key vocabulary to help you learn easily.\nCovers major phonological rules including liaison, tensification, aspiration, and nasalization.\nPractice natural pronunciation with frequently used real-life vocabulary.\nLearn to understand and accurately reproduce Korean speakers' pronunciation patterns.",
    "slideTitle3": "Grammar Basics",
    "slideDesc3": "Master Korean tenses and particles through foundational vocabulary and expressions.\nLearn essential particles like 은/는, 이/가, 을/를 and past, present, and future tenses.\nPractice real usage through example sentences and exercises for each grammar point.\nNaturally learn the characteristics of Korean word order (Subject-Object-Verb).",
